Steps to Reproduce:

1. write some simple HTML code like 
&lt;div&gt;
    &lt;div style="color:red"&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

2. format the code -> the HTML formatting is different when you don't add the style attribute

- VSCode Version: 1.8.0
- OS Version: Any

VScode doesn't detect correctly instance type if class constructor is called with different number of arguments. 

Example:

```js
class Person{
    constructor(arg){
        this.arg = arg;
    }
}

let p1 = new Person(null);      //OK, p1 is type Person
let p2 = new Person();           //WRONG, p2 is type "any"
```

I think it is a little annoying to have to put null's all over the place

