After upgrading to VS Code 1.8 I notice that the debug adapter output is getting messed up. Specifically it seems new lines are being added after every output event? This means that if the debug adapter sends following sequence the result is displayed broken up in multiple lines:

```
{"type":"event","seq":15,"event":"output","body":{"category":"stdout","output":"expected "}}
{"type":"event","seq":16,"event":"output","body":{"category":"stdout","output":"\t"}}
{"type":"event","seq":17,"event":"output","body":{"category":"stdout","output":"1.0"}}
{"type":"event","seq":18,"event":"output","body":{"category":"stdout","output":"\t"}}
{"type":"event","seq":19,"event":"output","body":{"category":"stdout","output":"-1.0"}}
{"type":"event","seq":20,"event":"output","body":{"category":"stdout","output":"\t"}}
{"type":"event","seq":21,"event":"output","body":{"category":"stdout","output":"1.0"}}
{"type":"event","seq":22,"event":"output","body":{"category":"stdout","output":"\n"}}
```

